  "humanFeedback": "# Playtest Feedback\n\n## What Worked\n\n- Curious opening-room pacing is appropriate.\n\n## Bugs or Confusion\n\n- Passive observations were presented as too many separate actions.\n- One-use actions displayed redundant 1/1 counts.\n- Suit Air changed only when actions completed.\n- Home chat became too small when several actions were visible.\n- Air canisters could not be used from Inventory.\n- Tracing the captain's route left no next action or stated motivation.\n\n## Desired Edits\n\n- Use one orientation action followed by up to three short narrative beats.\n- Reserve buttons for concrete choices and explicitly state when a room is\n  exhausted.\n- Consume Suit Air continuously and tune its rate from measured route duration.\n- Keep action and chat panels equal height with independent scrolling.\n- Give carried items globally usable Inventory actions.\n- Keep every revealed route playable and state the character's immediate goal.\n\nThe first run spent about 53 acting seconds between pressurizing the suit and\nthe newly completed captain's-quarters arrival route. At -105/min, that path\nuses 92.75 air and arrives with 7.25 before optional canister use.\n"
